repro_supplement_4: Various ages from approximately age 25 until menopause by hysterectomy at age 52.  Unknown what the cause was but I have had a history of fibroids.
menopause_symp: My problems with hot flashes have been minor, but happen alot at night causing sleeping problems.  I have also developed problems not being able to fall and stay asleep.  I had a period where I had to deal with a frozen shoulder, and have had near constant bouts of depression ever since menopause started.  Also, I don't know if it is connected, but I have been near paralyzed with the inability to take care of day to day necessary daily chores.  I get frozen with fear.
meno_impact: Parts of it have been debilitating to me.  I knew to expect hot flashes, but they haven't really been that much of an issue for me.  The worst parts of menopause have been the sleep problems, the overwhelming depression, and the fear/inability I have dealing with day to day tasks.  My inability to do these things has caused me problems with my home.
meno_difficult: The depression has been the worst thing to deal with.  I constantly want to cry and it's hard to get anything done.  It's also made me lose interest in things I love.
meno_treatment2: I was prescribed Paxel for my hot flashes, but had to stop taking it because it was leaving me emotionless.  Since then I have been put on Wellbutrin and Prozac for my depression.
meno_doctors: I wish there were more options to deal with symptoms for those of us that can't partake in HRT.
meno_younger: I would tell them about more of the symptoms that can occur.  I don't think that I was ever told about anything but hot flashes.  The sleeplessness, the depression, the anxiety and frozen shoulder was all a bit of a shock.
meno_peers: I would tell them to go to their doctors for help as soon as they can.  I waited and suffered too long before seeking help.
meno_advice: I really don't feel like I've received any advice.  Everything always focuses on HRT and as I can't have that, I've constantly been told I just have to live with it.
meno_mothermeno: Only minor hot flashes.
research_why: Menopause had been rough for me, and I was surprised at how little information and help was available.  I want to participate because I feel that there is so much more needs to be done for women's health issues.
